OL,3,CInflation no longer burns white hot -
OL,4,Cbut it's still glowing
OL,6,FThe key question is to what degree the
OL,7,Frise in inflation we are currently
OL,8,Fexperiencing is down to the way it is
OL,9,Fcalculated and to what degree it
OL,10,Freflects a resurgence in prices.
OL,12,FThe statisticians at the Office for
OL,13,FNational Statistics (ONS) measure the
OL,14,Fheadline rate of inflation by
OL,15,Fcomparing the change in prices across
OL,16,Fthe economy at two moments in time -
OL,17,Fin this instance November 2023 and
OL,18,F2024.
