OL,3,CInflation no longer burns white hot -
OL,4,Cbut it's still glowing
OL,6,FBut these are reasons to be concerned
OL,7,Fhere. "Core" inflation - which strips
OL,8,Faway the price of more volatile items
OL,9,Flike food and energy - rose to 3.5% in
OL,10,Fa way the Bank of England wants
OL,11,Fexpected.
OL,13,FInflation in the services sector of
OL,14,Fthe economy remained lodged at 5%
OL,16,FThe economy is stuck in a growth rut
OL,17,Fbut firms are still having to compete
OL,18,Fto attract workers and pay increases
OL,19,Fare not slowing as quickly as the Bank
OL,20,Fhoped.
