OL,3,CInflation no longer burns white hot -
OL,4,Cbut it's still glowing
OL,6,FShops, bars, pubs and restaurants face
OL,7,Fdramatically higher overheads after
OL,8,Fthe Chancellor chose to increase
OL,9,FNational Insurance contributions for
OL,10,Femployers and the National Living Wage.
OL,12,FSome will raise their prices, others
OL,13,Fcan't. Some may decide to let staff
OL,14,Fgo, while others may simply accept
OL,15,Flower profits.
